article.headline: Belmont 82, Middle Tennessee 69
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Alex Renfroe scored a game-high 25 points and was one of four Belmont players to score in double figures in an 82-69 win against Middle Tennessee on Wednesday night. Andy Wicke scored 22 points, Matthew Dotson added 15 and Shane Dansby chipped in with 10 for the Bruins (4-3). Renfroe was 11-for-13 from the free-throw line, and Wicke was 6-for-10 from beyond the arc. Four players also scored in double digits for the Blue Raiders (4-5), as Kevin Kanaskie tallied 15 points, Demetrius Green added 14 and Montarrio Haddock and Desmond Yates poured in 13 apiece. Belmont stayed ahead throughout the game, including a 44-31 halftime lead over Middle Tennessee. Each team grabbed 28 rebounds in the contest, but the Bruins hit 12 of 28 3-pointers compared to a 6-of-15 mark for the Blue Raiders.
